or UROX. A mild porphyric response was observed in the presence of iron loading and 5-aminolevulinic acid (ALA; a heme precursor) in AHR-/- mice, indicating that CYP1A2 induction is not absolutely necessary, but that constitutive CYP1A2 levels are sufficient for UROX under certain conditions[9].", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:49:28 +0000 2026"}